<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n16016i"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n16" href="#n16016i">N16 (VI.D.1)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n16all.htm#n16016i"> 16(i)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> offensive gm / salient / respirator <font face="wake">H</font></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"> On the nights of March 11th to March 14th, 1918, just before the great <mark>offensive</mark> of March 21st, the <mark>Germans</mark> fired 150,000 mustard gas shells into the villages and valleys of the Cambrai <mark>salient</mark>, an area of about twenty square miles, the same as that of central London. This caused 4,500 casualties, of whom only fifty died (all of them because they took off their <mark>respirators</mark> too soon). <small> J.B.S. Haldane, <a name="CHEM" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#CHEM"><cite title="source">Callinicus</cite></a> (1925) 55-6</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c02138i" href="c02all.htm#c02138i">VI.C.02:138(i)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
